PostProjectionVerticalOffset:
this value will be added to resulting location's Z axis. Can be useful when
    projecting points to navigation since navmesh is just an approximation of level
    geometry and items may end up being under collide-able geometry which would
    for example falsify visibility tests.
SerializedChannel: geometry trace channel for serialization purposes
bTraceComplex: if set, trace will run on complex collisions
bOnlyBlockingHits: if set, trace will look only for blocking hits
bCanTraceOnNavMesh: if set, editor will allow picking navmesh trace
bCanTraceOnGeometry: if set, editor will allow picking geometry trace
bCanProjectDown: if set, editor show height up/down properties for projection
